| Letter | Meaning |
| ------ | ------- |
| C      | Create  |
| R      | Read    |
| U      | Update  |
| D      | Delete  |


3. WHAT IS REST?

REST is a STYLE/RULE for creating backend APIs.

REST says:
| Method    | Work        |
| --------- | ----------- |
| GET       | Read data   |
| POST      | Create data |
| PUT/PATCH | Update data |
| DELETE    | Delete data |

NOW UNDERSTAND RESTFUL API CLEARLY
| METHOD | ROUTE           | PURPOSE        |
| ------ | --------------- | -------------- |
| GET    | `/students`     | Read students  |
| POST   | `/students`     | Create student |
| PUT    | `/students/:id` | Update student |
| DELETE | `/students/:id` | Delete student |
